Activity 5: colorful watercolor sillohuete
Age Group: 2-5

Category(s): sensory exploration, motor coordination, color mixing and painting techniques. 

Overview: 
Materials: Black construction paper, watercolor paper, watercolor paints, brushes, pencil, and scissors
Instructions:  Ask students to draw an image (animal, object, person, etc.) on the black construction paper and cut it out. They then stick this silhouette onto the watercolor paper.
Now, they can paint around the silhouette with watercolors, creating a vibrant background
Learning Goals:  promote creativity and understanding of contrast in art. It also strengthens fine motor skills and attention to detail.

ADApt:  
Monserrat's Tip: cut the shape several times in different shades to make a pattern could be fun

